===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|pes}}, {{m|enm|pais}}, {{m|enm|pees}}, borrowed from {{bor|en|xno|peis}} and {{bor|en|fro|pais||peace}}, from {{der|en|la|pāx||peace}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*paḱ-||to fasten, stick, place}}, related to {{cog|la|pacīscor||agree, stipulate}}, {{cog|la|pangō||fasten, fix}}; see {{l|en|pact}}. Displaced native {{cog|enm|frith}}, {{m|enm|frede||peace}} (from {{cog|ang|friþ}}, {{m|ang|frēod||peace}}), {{cog|enm|sib|sib, sibbe|peace}} (from {{cog|ang|sibb||peace, kinship}}), {{cog|enm|grith||peace, security}} (from {{cog|ang|griþ}} and {{cog|non|grið}}), {{cog|enm|saught|saht, saught|peace, reconciliation}} (from {{cog|ang|seht}}, {{m|ang|sæht||peace, pact, agreement}}). {{doublet|en|pax}}.

